    "recap_headline": "Rutgers University",
    "recap_text": "CHAMPAIGN, Ill. \u2013\nRutgers baseball won the series finale over Illinois by a score of 8-3 on Sunday afternoon at Illinois Field.\nThe Scarlet Knights (13-10, 3-3) erased an early 3-0 deficit with eight unanswered to beat\u00a0the Fighting Illini (12-10, 4-5) and avoid a series sweep.\nIn the bottom of the third, Illinois scored twice on a pair of RBI groundouts. An RBI double made it 3-0 in the fourth.\nIn the top of the sixth, a sac fly from\nYomar Carreras\ngot Rutgers on the board at 3-1. The Scarlet Knights then rallied for five runs in the seventh to flip the game and take control.\nAfter RU loaded the bases,\nJulius Rosado\ndrew a walk to score a run.\nPeyton Bonds\nthen laced a bases-clearing double to left, scoring three to give Rutgers a 5-3 advantage. Carreras added a single right after to bring in Bonds and push the lead to 6-3.\nMatt Chatelle\nsingled with the bases loaded in the ninth, scoring two more to make it 8-3.\nVincent Borghese\nstarted for Rutgers and delivered 4.1 innings, giving up three runs on five hits with four strikeouts. After two men reached in the fifth,\nChris Sand\ncame in the game and got the last two outs to strand the runners and end the frame.\nSand would go on to pitch his best game as a Scarlet Knight, finishing off the victory with 4.2 scoreless innings and earning the win. He allowed just one hit and struck out a pair to help Rutgers control the remainder of the contest.\nOffensively, Bonds finished the day with two hits, three RBIs and two runs scored.\nTrey Wells\nand\u00a0Chatelle both collected multi-hit games as well.\nRutgers returns home this week, beginning with a midweek contest against Delaware at 3 p.m. Tuesday at Bainton Field.\nFollow Rutgers Baseball on Social Media\nX\n|\nInstagram\n|\nFacebook",
